  "instructions": [
    "Mix spring onions, sugar, and salt in a bowl to create the fermented mixture.",
    "Pour the mixture into a jar and add water, leaving 1 inch of space at the top.",
    "Seal the jar and let it ferment at room temperature for 2-3 days.",
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Toast the bread slices for 5-7 minutes or until crispy.",
    "Butter or oil the toasted bread slices.",
    "Top each slice with a fermented spring onion and a sprinkle of parsley.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
